Step 1 — Establish the three-panel shell
Replace the current 2-col layout with a fixed frame that never scrolls as a whole. The panels scroll independently.


┌─────────────┬──────────────────────────┬─────────────────────┐
│  LEFT        │  CENTER                  │  RIGHT (drawer)     │
│  240px fixed │  flex-1, min-w-0         │  360px, slide-in    │
│  overflow-y  │  overflow-y              │  overflow-y         │
│  auto        │  auto                    │  auto               │
└─────────────┴──────────────────────────┴─────────────────────┘
The outer container is height: 100vh (or the main content area height), display: flex, overflow: hidden. Nothing scrolls globally. Each panel manages its own scroll.

The right drawer starts at width: 0 / opacity: 0 and transitions to width: 360px when a set is activated. Use CSS transform: translateX not width animation for performance.

Step 2 — Build the Left Navigator
This replaces the current right-panel comp sets list. It's compact and persistent.

Structure:


