Instruments can be removed from the set here (checkbox + action button)
The grid in the drawer is independent from the search grid — separate selection state
Step 5 — The Sticky Selection Tray
This is the key UX unlock. It appears at the bottom of the center panel only when rows are selected in the search grid.


┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ✓ 3 instruments selected    [×]                       │
│  Add to:  [EJB ×]  [SSA Comps ×]  [+ Select set ▾]   │
│                                         [ADD TO SETS]  │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
Behavior:

Slides up from bottom when selectedRows.length > 0
Slides back down when selection is cleared (ESC or clicking ×)
"Add to" chips are the target comp sets — pre-populated with the currently active set
+ Select set opens a small popover with the comp set list (not a full dropdown)
ADD TO SETS is disabled until ≥1 set is chosen
After adding: tray shows a success state for ~2s then clears selection
This is the fix for the "invisible add flow." The action is now anchored to the selection, not floating disconnected above the grid.

Step 6 — Persistent Context Indicator
Add a subtle context banner at the top of the center panel, below the search controls:


Currently viewing:  EJB  (17 instruments)    [Open set ↗]
Visible only when a set is active
Open set reopens the right drawer if it was closed
This gives new users an answer to "wait, what set am I adding to right now?"
Step 7 — Interaction flow for the "add" task (before vs after)
Before (current):

Search left
Shift-select rows in grid (left, unclear affordance)
Find dropdown above grid (left, disconnected)
Select comp set in dropdown
Click ADD TO COMP SETS button
Switch eyes right to verify it appeared
After (hybrid):

Search center
Check rows (checkbox column, clear affordance)
Tray appears at bottom automatically
Target sets already pre-filled with active set — confirm or adjust
Click ADD
Badge count in left navigator increments — verified without eye movement
Step 8 — Responsive / collapsed behavior
At narrower viewports (1280px and below):

Left navigator collapses to icon-only strip (just set initials + badge count)
Tooltip on hover shows full name
Right drawer becomes a bottom sheet on mobile (if applicable)
Implementation order
#	Task	Why first
1	Three-panel shell + left navigator	Everything depends on this frame
2	Right drawer component	Unblocks removing inline expansion
3	Sticky tray	Unblocks removing the old add-flow controls
4	Context indicator banner	Small, high-value for new users
5	Rename inline editing	Last because it's pure detail polish
